This solution works by checking if the word concatenated `k+1` times is a substring of the sequence. It starts with `k = 0` and increments `k` as long as the condition is true. The loop exits when `word * (k + 1)` is no longer found in the sequence, and the function returns the last valid `k`, which is the maximum k-repeating value.
